news.title: Marble waste a major environmental issue in Rajsamand
news.para: Although there have been several attempts to put slurry to gainful use such as making bricks out of it or using it in road construction, the efforts have not been successful so far. But the search is on.

news.title: Land acquisition notification for five Kochi metro stations
news.para: The notification was issued for the acquisition of land for the proposed stations at Palarivattom Junction, Kakkanad, Cochin SEZ, Chitethukara and Kinfra.

news.title: Buda invites tender for new master plan of Belagavi
news.para: The old master plan, approved in 2014, covers Belagavi and surrounding 27 villages. A total of 28 villages are going to be added in the new master plan of BUDA.

news.title: In relief to owners, Odisha government notifies Apartment Act
news.para: The Act, which aims to ensure better management of apartments in a housing complex, got the governor’s consent on October 27. The bill was tabled in the assembly by housing and urban development minister Usha Devi on September 25.

news.title: Income tax department searches real estate firms in Gujarat
news.para: According to sources close to the development, about 150 IT officers along with personnel from Ahmedabad and other centres in Gujarat searched commercial and residential properties belonging to the three companies.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC asks builders, contractors to follow dust mitigation norms or face action
news.para: ​​The BMC communication covers contractors and real estate firms in the P North civic ward in western Mumbai, mainly suburb of Malad, as the civic body seek to improve Mumbai's Air Quality Index (AQI).

news.title: Rs 24.30-lakh fine imposed on 39 GRAP violations in Noida
news.para: The Noida authority said in a statement it imposed penalties worth Rs 13.80 lakh on 26 entities flouting GRAP guidelines. The authority said its 14 teams are daily inspecting construction sites, roads and open spaces to ensure compliance of the GRAP rules.

news.title: Competition Commission to conduct market study on cement sector in India
news.para: ​According to CCI, given the criticality of cement for many vital sectors, well-functioning and competitive cement market is of utmost importance.

news.title: Mumbai: Developers must now give additional area to rehabilitation tenants
news.para: The fungible compensation area is 35% of the total built-up area and was introduced in 2012. It is offered free of premium to the builder to enable the provision of larger homes—with 105sqft carpet area in addition to the minimum 300sqft carpet area to be given in a rehab flat.

news.title: Netflix renews office lease in BKC, to pay Rs 284 crore rentals over five years
news.para: The company will be paying monthly rentals of nearly Rs 4.30 crore for two separate leases executed through Netflix Entertainment Services India LLP. The office space is spread across two units – on the 11th and 12th floors - of the commercial tower.

news.title: GIC Housing Finance's net profit declines 46.39% in Q2 FY24
news.para: GIC Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 270.19 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 3.81 per cent from Rs 280.89 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Crompton Greaves Consumer Electricals' net profit dips 22.83% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Crompton Greaves Consumer Electricals' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,797.15 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 4.62 per cent from Rs 1,717.80 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Toronto home sales fall for fifth straight month in October 2023
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales fell 5% in October from September, extending a string of declines since June, Toronto Regional Real Estate Board (TRREB) data showed on Thursday.

news.title: Lendlease, Google end development deals for $15 billion San Francisco Bay Area projects
news.para: Lendlease bagged the contract from Google in 2019 to develop the $15 billion worth of residential and retail space in Sunnyvale, San Jose and Mountain View, which could ultimately bring about 15,000 new housing units to the region.

news.title: National Association of Realtors' CEO steps down
news.para: "Bob Goldberg, who announced his planned retirement in June of this year, will serve as an executive consultant to NAR to help support the transition," it said, adding that it is conducting a comprehensive search process to identify a permanent CEO.

news.title: Vonovia CEO says capital increase less likely after property sale
news.para: Vonovia had said in recent months it had enough flexibility to avoid a capital increase, but market speculation that it may need to resort to such a measure had persisted.

news.title: Indigo Paints' net profit dips 31.72% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Indigo Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 282.18 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 14.81 per cent from Rs 245.79 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: GRAP III invoked, non-essential construction work banned in Delhi
news.para: The Centre's pollution control panel invoked the GRAP III on Thursday, directing a halt on non-essential construction work, stone crushing and mining in Delhi-NCR.

news.title: Noida administration says will enforce GRAP III, to ban construction
news.para: ​The ban will not be on exempted essential works but only on those where applicable, District Magistrate Manish Kumar Verma said, citing guidelines of the Centre's Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) in the National Capital Region and Adjoining Areas.

news.title: Orient Electric posts net profit of Rs 18.45 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Orient Electric's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 570.26 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 10.29 per cent from Rs 517.06 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
